author: HelloFresh
course: main course
time required: 40 minutes
---

Wash and dry all produce. Place rack in upper third of oven and preheat to 425 degrees. Line a #baking sheet{} with aluminum foil and brush with a drizzle of oil. Trim @scallions{2}. Finely mince whites; thinly slice greens. Zest 1 tsp zest from @lime{1}, then cut into 6 wedges. Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}.

Peel @carrots{2}. Using your #peeler{}, shave carrots lengthwise into thin ribbons and place in a #medium bowl{} along with scallion greens, lime zest, juice from two lime wedges, half the @honey{1%tablespoon}, and a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon}. Toss to combine and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Gently mix @ground beef{10%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, scallion whites, 1 tsp shallot, @Moo Shu spice blend{1%teaspoon}, @sriracha{1%teaspoon}, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and pepper in another medium bowl. Shape into 1 1/2-inch-wide meatballs (you should have about 10). Transfer to lined #baking sheet{}. Bake in oven until browned, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #small lidded pot{} over medium-high heat. Add remaining shallot and cook, stirring, until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Add @jasmine rice{3/4%cup} and @water{1 1/4%cups}. Season with salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, then stir, cover, lower heat, and reduce heat to a gentle simmer. Cook until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Stir together @hoisin sauce{1%ounce}, @sriracha{1/2%tsp}, remaining honey, juice from two lime wedges, and @water{1%tablespoon} in a #small bowl{}. Once meatballs are browned, remove from oven and brush with hoisin mixture. Return sheet to oven and bake until glaze is tacky and has lost some of its shine, about ~{5%minutes}. Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between two #bowls{} and top with meatballs. Using a #rubber spatula{}, scrape up any excess glaze from sheet and drizzle onto meatballs. Arrange carrot salad on top and drizzle with marinating liquid, if desired. Serve with remaining lime wedges and sriracha.

> Add up to 1 TBSP water to sheet to loosen glaze if needed.